The paper discusses the implementation of a prototype framework for monitoring Erlang/OTP gen_server applications against multiparty session types, which involves formalizing communication patterns in actor-based applications. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Programming Languages (cs.PL), Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC), Software Engineering (cs.SE), Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS), and Logic in Computer Science (cs.LO) sub-categories.
